\begin_layout Section
Enrichment 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Enrichment analysis consists in a quantitative measure to infer if the values
 of a biological condition (e.g.
 fold changes) shows statistically significant, concordant values or increased
 proportion for a particular set of biological annotations (module or gene
 set).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
How is this calculated ?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Currently there are three different methods for enrichment analysis implemented
 in Gitools.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
