\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Z-score test
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To use the Z-score test a Continous Data Matrix is needed.
 Gitools tests if there is a significant deviation from random expectation
 for an estimator value (mean or median) of each module in each condition:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{i}=\frac{(X-\mu_{i})}{\sigma_{i}}$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the mean, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the standard deviation.
\end_layout

